div.p:
24. Your April 8, 4 p.m. Department approves presentation of memorandum transmitted with your despatch of April 5, and presentation of memorandum as outlined in your telegram, except
for last paragraph of concluding portion. It desires that this paragraph should read as follows:
“The compliance with this patriotic duty, the incorporation into the budget for 1921–23 [1922–23?] of the necessary reforms, the congressional approval of that budget before June 30th next, would be heralded by my government as a real demonstration in this field of successful republican government in Cuba. The failure to give that demonstration under so clear a necessity would be fatal to the possibility of averting imminent financial disaster to the Cuban Treasury, and could not but be regarded by my Government with the gravest concern.”
